<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_sending_an_e_mail_template_to_a_customer">3.1. Sending an E-mail template to a customer</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can use event procedures to automatically send <strong><em>E-mail templates</em></strong> to your <strong><em>customers</em></strong> when certain events occur. Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » Email » Templates</strong> to set up <strong>E-mail templates</strong>. You can send your customers:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>order confirmations</strong> to let them know that you <strong><em>received the order</em></strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>messages</strong> if the customer paid the <strong><em>wrong amount</em></strong>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
